    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Items comprising incense in wax or another carrier, resembling the head of a large nail, that are attached to the pascal candle during the Christian Easter Vigil rites. The incense may be in the form of a nail or a nail head attached to a tack-like point, used to secure it to the candle. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
